Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}; reserve a pinch in
a small #bowl{} (you'll use it in Step 5). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2},
separating whites from greens. Thinly slice @jalapeño{1} into rounds, removing ribs
and seeds for less heat; mince a few rounds until you have @?minced jalapeño{1%tsp}.

> Use 2 tsp minced jalapeño for more heat, especially for 4 servings.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a small #pot{} over medium heat. Add scallion
whites, remaining garlic, and ½ tsp @Fajita Spice Blend{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring,
until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Use 1 tsp Fajita Spice Blend for 4 servings.

Add @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1%cup}, and a pinch
of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until
water is absorbed and bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> Use 2 cups water for 4 servings.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

In a second small microwave-safe bowl, combine sliced jalapeño, juice from half the
lime, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cover with plastic wrap and
microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

> For 4 servings, use ½ tsp sugar and the whole lime.

Pat @bavette steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with remaining
Fajita Spice Blend, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until
browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}
to rest.

> Swap in chicken or steak for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through,
3-5 minutes per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

== Creamy Salsa Verde ==

To #bowl{} with reserved garlic, add @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, a
squeeze of lime juice, a big pinch of lime zest, and a pinch of minced jalapeño to
taste. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> If you like some zesty heat, add a small splash of jalapeño pickling liquid
in place of, or in addition to, lime juice.

== Assembly ==

Fluff bulgur with a #fork{}. Stir in tomato, half the scallion greens, remaining lime
zest, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much remaining minced jalapeño as you like.
Season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice steak crosswise.

> Thinly slice chicken or steak against the grain.

Divide bulgur between shallow #bowls{}; top with steak. Drizzle everything with
crema; garnish with remaining scallion greens and as much pickled jalapeño
(draining first) as you like. Serve.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.